Match State: Stumps - Day 1

Hello and welcome to the start of the second day's play of the third Ashes Test at Old Trafford

Australia clawed their way back with some late wickets towards the end of the first day

But England are still well placed at 341/5 with Andrew Flintoff about to come to the crease

Ian Bell defended stoutly to begin with and grew more confident and fluent as the day wore on, playing some delectable cover drives

The first ball will be bowled soon enough so don't go too far

I'm Anand Vasu, your commentator, and will be more than happy to call the play for you today

The players are on the field now

The local hero Andrew Flintoff is walking out to bat and Old Trafford roars in appreciation

Play is about to get under way. Fasten your seat-belts!

It is Ian Bell on strike. Glenn 'Pigeon' McGrath has the ball in his hand and is good to go
